Defendant in custody on another matter.
Count 1 - Deliver Schedule II Narcotics (Morphine) - No contest plea.  Convicted.   
Count 6 - Deliver Schedule II Narcotics (Fentanyl) - No contest plea.  Convicted.
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 - 5.  Motion granted.   
Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years concurrent with the probation ordered in Forest County Case 15 CF 5.  Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process and follow through;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) On Count 1, submit DNA sample;
5) On Count 1, repay $400.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
6) On Count 1, spend twelve (12) months in the Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, concurrent with condition time in Forest County Case 15 CF 5.  Huber should include counseling as deemed appropriate by the agent;
7) Pay costs of action (apply bail);
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant is entitled to 2 days sentence credit should probation be revoked.
Minutes.
